The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Asia Cup right after India tour

Karachi: The Asia Cup will be held right after Indias tour of Pakistan. 

According to Salim Altaf, PCBs director (cricket operations) India will arrive in Pakistan in the first week of January next year and finish the series by February 15. 

?The series will certainly end on February 15 and the six-nation Asia Cup will begin on February 18,? Altaf said from Lahore. 

India are scheduled to play three Tests and five one-day Internationals. They are likely to arrive in Pakistan less than two weeks after England complete their first tour of Pakistan since 2000. 

